{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must implement "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIApplicationDelegate.application(_:continue:restorationHandler:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to handle your universal links. By default, the Appcues iOS SDK will call this method for every "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https"},{"type":"text","text":" link it tries to open to allow your app a chance to handle it internally instead of opening the link in a browser. Optionally, you may provide an allow list of URL hosts—refer to the Domain Allow List section below."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app has opted into "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/app_and_environment\/scenes"},{"type":"text","text":", you still must implement the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIApplicationDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":" method to handle universal links triggered from the Appcues iOS SDK."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Implementing-the-NSUserActivity-Handler","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Implementing the NSUserActivity Handler"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIApplicationDelegate.application(_:continue:restorationHandler:)"},{"type":"text","text":" must return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if you’ve successfully handled the link and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" otherwise."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If needed, you can identify links coming from the Appcues iOS SDK by a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"referrer"},{"type":"text","text":" property in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSUserActivity.userInfo"},{"type":